#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:2 2f24e39cab1e48aaa740f4de7c9205c4
msgid "Basics & Visualization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:4 4c34dcbdf51f41e58b0623faa5804022
msgid ""
"Four short scripts in ``examples/basics/`` that visualize the building "
"blocks of FEM in TensorMesh: where interpolation nodes sit on the "
"reference element, what the shape functions look like, how internal node "
"numbering compares to Gmsh / VTK, and what the mesh generators produce. "
"None of these scripts solve a PDE — they exist to make the underlying "
"objects tangible and to sanity-check the conventions used elsewhere in "
"the library."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:12 cf6854a0a2ec43db89b14cdf2dec55bc
msgid ""
"If you are reading this page after the "
":doc:`../user_guide/elements_and_quadrature` user-guide page, treat these"
" scripts as the picture book that goes with it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:18 7af96709fffc49c08f968005966ddb06
msgid "Interpolation nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:20 669f63eedabf4f909354760464590506
msgid ""
"``examples/basics/basis.py`` plots the spatial distribution of "
"interpolation (Lagrange) nodes on the reference element for all seven "
"element classes — :class:`~tensormesh.Line`, "
":class:`~tensormesh.Triangle`, :class:`~tensormesh.Quadrilateral`, "
":class:`~tensormesh.Tetrahedron`, :class:`~tensormesh.Hexahedron`, "
":class:`~tensormesh.Pyramid`, :class:`~tensormesh.Prism` — at orders 1 "
"through 4. The driver is a one-liner per element class:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:28 11ff53dc9cd44f639603f093ebbeae05
msgid "examples/basics/basis.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:42 3084a8d4f7a64b2d813abd6c32d93fe0
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The number of basis points grows quickly with order: :math:`(p+1)^d` for "
"tensor elements, :math:`\\binom{p+d}{d}` for simplex elements. Knowing "
"where they sit is the first sanity check when something goes wrong with a"
" higher-order solve."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:48 418bcc35b15746d99b7b1ca0087de060
msgid ""
"The seven panels below show the Lagrange-node layout for every supported "
"element class at orders 1–4. Each panel reads left-to-right by order; "
"node indices match the internal ``element.get_basis(order)`` ordering."
msgstr ""

