#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:253 f29eb8ffb10c4ad8af02d983237c8593
msgid ""
"``examples/basics/plot_mesh.py`` is the picture catalog of what "
"TensorMesh's mesh tools can produce, plus a few visualization helpers "
"from :mod:`tensormesh.visualization`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:257 37d2472c7463400ca326ea5c7c612a17
msgid ""
"**Built-in primitives** — rectangle (triangle and quadrilateral), cube "
"(tetrahedral and hexahedral, the latter with quadratic basis), and a unit"
" disk via :class:`~tensormesh.MeshGen`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:260 ce7bf494fd264e2ebf3dfee3f41cc284
msgid ""
"**Hybrid meshes** — half the rectangle is meshed with triangles, the "
"other half with quadrilaterals, and a circular hole is punched in the "
"interface. ``mesh.cells`` is a ``BufferDict`` keyed by element type, so "
"all assemblers iterate over both element types automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:265 aaeb18f2d40a4a96b5c6f1d2f7a7e7af
msgid ""
"**Adjacency graphs** — node-to-node and element-to-element connectivity "
"drawn over the mesh, in 2D and 3D. Useful for debugging coloring and "
"partitioning algorithms (see :doc:`distributed`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/basics.rst:269 220cd86ccc6647548b6d1854e7cb4770
msgid ""
"**Field visualization** — scalar fields painted as nodal values "
"(interpolated to the mesh) or as per-element constants."
msgstr ""

